# Spec: JSON Schemas (Examples)

This document provides example JSON structures for the core data objects used in the RUR 1.0 protocol.

### **Truth Packet (Example)**
```json
{
  "org_id": "org_123",
  "role_id": "role_456",
  "rotation_12m_bucket": "10-20",
  "overtime_median_bucket": "2-5",
  "overtime_paid": true,
  "work_mode": "hybrid",
  "onsite_days_bucket": "2-3",
  "role_tenure_bucket": "12-24",
  "retention_90d_bucket": "70-85",
  "attestation": "I declare truthfulness and accept sampling audit.",
  "signature": "SD-JWT|BBS+"
}
```

### **Needs Capsule (Example)**
```json
{
  "candidate_id": "cand_abc",
  "non_negotiables": {
    "salary_min": 12000,
    "work_mode": "remote",
    "flex_hours": true,
    "availability": "9-15 CET"
  },
  "preferences": {
    "mentoring": true,
    "communication_style": "async",
    "growth_tempo": "steady"
  },
  "ai_assist_used": true
}
```

### **VRF Receipt (Example)**
```json
{
  "application_hash": "0xabcdef...",
  "drand_round": 123456,
  "beacon": "...",
  "lane": "L",
  "shortlisted": true,
  "verify_url": "[https://example.org/verify?hash=0xabcdef...&round=123456](https://example.org/verify?hash=0xabcdef...&round=123456)"
}
```